as what sort of face, leg, foot, teeth, hair, he has.
Thus he who engages66 to his citizens to take care of the city, the empire, and Italy, and the sanctuaries of the gods, forces every mortal to be so­ licitous, and to ask from what sire he is descended, or whether he is base- by the obscurity of his mother.
What ?
do you, the son of a Syrus,67 a Dama, or a Dionysius, dare to cast down the citizens of Rome from the [Tarpeian] rock, or de­ liver them up to Cadmus [the executioner] ?
