May the gods and goddesses, 0 Damasippus, present you with a barber for your sound advice!
But by what means did you get so well acquainted with me?
Since all my fortunes were dissipated at the middle of the Exchange,26 detached from all business of my own, I mind that of other people.
For formerly I used to take a delight in inquiring, in what vase the crafty Sisyphus might have washed his feet;
what was carved in an unworkmanlike manner, and what more roughly cast than it ought to be;
